<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{6}{y}={0}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{3}{x}+{5}{y}={16}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2},{2}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+-{6}{y}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}={0}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{0}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3}{\left(\frac{{{0}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{6}}}}\right)}+{5}{y}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{3}}{{-{{6}}}}\cdot{\left({0}\right)}--\frac{{3}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}+{5}{y}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0}-{\left({3}\right)}{y}+{5}{y}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{y}+{\left({5}\right)}{y}={16}-{0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{y}+{\left({5}\right)}{y}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({3}+{\left({5}\right)}\right)}{y}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{y}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{16}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={2}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+-{6}{\left({2}\right)}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{\left(-{12}\right)}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}={0}-{\left(-{12}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}={12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{12}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2},{2}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

